# Form Validation UX

Create forms that guide users with timely, accessible feedback without being intrusive.

## Default Behavior

### Validate on Blur, Show Errors on Touch

Don't show errors while the user is still typing. Wait until they leave the field.

```typescript
// ✅ Default: Show error only when touched and invalid
isInvalid(field: string): boolean {
  const control = this.form.get(field);
  return !!(control?.invalid && control?.touched);
}
```

```html
<!-- ✅ Default: Conditional error display -->
@if (isInvalid('email')) {
  <span class="error" role="alert">
    {{ getErrorMessage('email') }}
  </span>
}
```

### Minimum Character Threshold for Search/Filter

Don't trigger search until the user has typed enough characters to produce meaningful results.

```typescript
// ✅ Default: 3-character minimum for search
searchHint = computed(() => {
  const term = store.searchTerm().trim();
  if (term.length > 0 && term.length < 3) {
    return `Type ${3 - term.length} more character${3 - term.length > 1 ? 's' : ''} to search`;
  }
  return null;
});

filteredItems = computed(() => {
  const term = store.searchTerm().toLowerCase().trim();
  if (term.length < 3) return store.items();  // Don't filter yet
  // ... apply filter
});
```

### Accessible Error Messages

Link errors to inputs with ARIA attributes.

```html
<!-- ✅ Default: Accessible form field -->
<div class="form-field">
  <label for="email">
    Email <span aria-hidden="true">*</span>
  </label>
  <input
    id="email"
    type="email"
    formControlName="email"
    [attr.aria-invalid]="isInvalid('email')"
    [attr.aria-describedby]="isInvalid('email') ? 'email-error' : null"
  />
  @if (isInvalid('email')) {
    <span id="email-error" class="error" role="alert">
      {{ getErrorMessage('email') }}
    </span>
  }
</div>
```

## Rationale

1. **Reduced frustration** - Users aren't interrupted while typing.
2. **Clear feedback** - Errors appear at the right moment (after interaction).
3. **Accessibility** - Screen readers announce errors via `role="alert"` and `aria-describedby`.
4. **Performance** - Minimum character thresholds prevent unnecessary processing.

## Documented Exceptions

### 1. Real-Time Validation for Specific Fields

Show validation status as user types for fields where immediate feedback is valuable.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Real-time password strength
passwordStrength = computed(() => {
  const password = this.form.get('password')?.value || '';
  if (password.length === 0) return null;
  if (password.length < 8) return 'weak';
  if (!/[A-Z]/.test(password) || !/[0-9]/.test(password)) return 'medium';
  return 'strong';
});
```

```html
<!-- ✅ Exception: Show strength while typing -->
@if (passwordStrength(); as strength) {
  <div class="password-strength" [class]="strength" aria-live="polite">
    Password strength: {{ strength }}
  </div>
}
```

### 2. Availability Check with Debounce

For username/email uniqueness, validate against API but with debounce.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Async availability check
ngOnInit() {
  this.form.get('username')?.valueChanges.pipe(
    debounceTime(500),
    distinctUntilChanged(),
    filter(value => value.length >= 3),
    switchMap(username => this.userService.checkAvailability(username)),
    takeUntilDestroyed(this.destroyRef)
  ).subscribe(isAvailable => {
    if (!isAvailable) {
      this.form.get('username')?.setErrors({ taken: true });
    }
  });
}
```

### 3. Lower Threshold for Specific Searches

Some searches work well with fewer characters (e.g., initials, short codes).

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: 2-character minimum for short identifiers
const MIN_SEARCH_LENGTH = searchType === 'employeeId' ? 2 : 3;
```

### 4. Instant Validation on Submit Attempt

Mark all fields as touched and show all errors when user tries to submit invalid form.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Show all errors on submit attempt
onSubmit() {
  if (this.form.invalid) {
    this.form.markAllAsTouched();  // Reveals all errors
    return;
  }
  // ... proceed with submission
}
```

## Anti-Patterns

```typescript
// ❌ Show errors while user is still typing
isInvalid(field: string): boolean {
  return !!this.form.get(field)?.invalid;  // Missing && touched
}

// ❌ No minimum threshold for search
filteredItems = computed(() => {
  const term = store.searchTerm();
  if (term) {  // Single character triggers filter!
    return items.filter(/* ... */);
  }
});

// ❌ Missing ARIA attributes
<input type="email" formControlName="email" />
@if (emailInvalid) {
  <span class="error">Invalid email</span>  // Not linked to input!
}

// ❌ Generic error messages
<span class="error">This field is invalid</span>

// ❌ No feedback on character threshold
// User types "jo" and nothing happens - confusing!
```

## Error Message Patterns

```typescript
// ✅ Specific, actionable error messages
getErrorMessage(field: string): string {
  const control = this.form.get(field);
  if (!control?.errors) return '';
  
  const errors = control.errors;
  const fieldName = this.getFieldLabel(field);
  
  if (errors['required']) return `${fieldName} is required`;
  if (errors['email']) return 'Please enter a valid email address';
  if (errors['minlength']) {
    const min = errors['minlength'].requiredLength;
    return `${fieldName} must be at least ${min} characters`;
  }
  if (errors['maxlength']) {
    const max = errors['maxlength'].requiredLength;
    return `${fieldName} must be no more than ${max} characters`;
  }
  if (errors['pattern']) return `${fieldName} format is invalid`;
  if (errors['taken']) return `This ${fieldName.toLowerCase()} is already in use`;
  
  return `${fieldName} is invalid`;
}
```

## Loading States in Forms

```html
<!-- ✅ Submit button with loading state -->
<button 
  type="submit" 
  [disabled]="form.invalid || isSubmitting()"
  [attr.aria-busy]="isSubmitting()"
>
  @if (isSubmitting()) {
    <span class="spinner" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    Saving...
  } @else {
    Save
  }
</button>
```

## Search Hint Pattern

```html
<!-- ✅ Guide user on minimum characters -->
<div class="search-group">
  <input
    type="search"
    placeholder="Search..."
    [value]="searchInput()"
    (input)="onSearchInput($event)"
    [attr.aria-describedby]="store.searchHint() ? 'search-hint' : null"
  />
  @if (store.searchHint(); as hint) {
    <span id="search-hint" class="search-hint" aria-live="polite">
      {{ hint }}
    </span>
  }
</div>
```

## Validation Timing Summary

| Validation Type | When to Validate | When to Show Error |
|-----------------|------------------|-------------------|
| Required | On blur | After touch |
| Format (email, phone) | On blur | After touch |
| Min/Max length | On input (for counter) | After touch |
| Password strength | On input | Always (as indicator) |
| Async (availability) | On input, debounced | After API response |
| Cross-field (confirm password) | On blur of either | After both touched |
| All fields | On submit attempt | Immediately |
